					<description><![CDATA[Right on! One name psychologists use for that nagging effect an unfinished task on our psyche is &quot;The Zeigarnik Effect.&quot; She discovered that a finished task has no effect, but one that&#039;s unfinished causes our unconscious mind to ping our conscious mind like a little kid reminding his mother to stop at McDonald&#039;s on the way home. Here&#039;s an article I wrote on the topic that adds this dimension: http://www.2time-sys.com/2013/06/17/emails-impact-on-our-stress-levels/]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Right on! One name psychologists use for that nagging effect an unfinished task on our psyche is &#8220;The Zeigarnik Effect.&#8221; She discovered that a finished task has no effect, but one that&#8217;s unfinished causes our unconscious mind to ping our conscious mind like a little kid reminding his mother to stop at McDonald&#8217;s on the way home. Here&#8217;s an article I wrote on the topic that adds this dimension: <a href="http://www.2time-sys.com/2013/06/17/emails-impact-on-our-stress-levels/" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.2time-sys.com/2013/06/17/emails-impact-on-our-stress-levels/</a></p>
