					<description><![CDATA[I&#039;ve heard the &quot;don&#039;t check your e-mail first thing&quot; advice many times and it&#039;s a non starter for me.  I always check my email first thing in the morning. I often work with people in earlier timezones so it&#039;s less productive for everyone if I wait until &quot;their&quot; afternoon. However I usually close down e-mail after about 30-40 minutes and then tackle the first big task.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I&#8217;ve heard the &#8220;don&#8217;t check your e-mail first thing&#8221; advice many times and it&#8217;s a non starter for me.  I always check my email first thing in the morning. I often work with people in earlier timezones so it&#8217;s less productive for everyone if I wait until &#8220;their&#8221; afternoon. However I usually close down e-mail after about 30-40 minutes and then tackle the first big task.</p>
